def calculate_objective(item_box_assignments: DSList(length=8, elem_type=DSInt()), nr_used_boxes: DSInt(lb=0, ub=8)) -> int:

    return nr_used_boxes

# --- Auxiliary Variables ---

def place_items_in_boxes(
    items: DSList(length=8, elem_type=Item),
    item_box_assignments: DSList(length=8, elem_type=DSInt()),
    x_y_positions: DSList(length=8, elem_type=BoxPosition),
    nr_used_boxes: DSInt(lb=0, ub=8)
) -> None:
    # Each item must be assigned to exactly one box
    for i in range(1, N_ITEMS + 1):
        assert item_box_assignments[i] >= 1
        assert item_box_assignments[i] <= nr_used_boxes
    
    # Positions must be within box boundaries
    for i in range(1, N_ITEMS + 1):
        item : Item = items[i]
        pos : BoxPosition = x_y_positions[i]
        assert pos.x >= 0
        assert pos.x <= BOX_WIDTH - item.width
        assert pos.y >= 0
        assert pos.y <= BOX_HEIGHT - item.height

def ensure_no_overlap(
    items: DSList(length=8, elem_type=Item),
    item_box_assignments: DSList(length=8, elem_type=DSInt()),
    x_y_positions: DSList(length=8, elem_type=BoxPosition),
    nr_used_boxes: DSInt(lb=0, ub=8)
) -> None:
    # Ensure no overlapping items within the same box
    for i in range(1, N_ITEMS + 1):
        for j in range(i + 1, N_ITEMS + 1):
            # Only check items in the same box
            if item_box_assignments[i] == item_box_assignments[j]:
                item_i : Item = items[i]
                item_j : Item = items[j]
                pos_i : BoxPosition = x_y_positions[i]
                pos_j : BoxPosition = x_y_positions[j]
                
                # Check for overlap in x-direction
                assert not (
                    (pos_i.x <= pos_j.x + item_j.width - 1) and
                    (pos_j.x <= pos_i.x + item_i.width - 1)
                ) or (
                    (pos_i.x >= pos_j.x + item_j.width - 1) and
                    (pos_j.x >= pos_i.x + item_i.width - 1)
                )
                
                # Check for overlap in y-direction

                ) or (
                    (pos_i.y >= pos_j.y + item_j.height - 1) and
                    (pos_j.y >= pos_i.y + item_i.height - 1)
                )
